    "body": "The code represents a useful pattern in normal mode where remapping `<tab>` will implicitly also remap `<c-i>` unless you remap that explicitly. This however relies on the _unmapped_ behavior being identical which is not true in terminal mode, as vterm can distinguish these keys.\r\n\r\nVim seems to entangle this with kitty keyboard mode detection which is irrelevant for us. Conditional fallbacks depending on keyboard mode could be done completely inside `vterm/` without `getchar.c` getting involved, I would think.\r\n\r\nref https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31926#issuecomment-2580000207",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Does that mean this part in Vim's terminal code is not relevant?\r\n```c\r\n    void\r\ncheck_no_reduce_keys(void)\r\n{\r\n    if (no_reduce_key_state != NRKS_CHECK\r\n\t    || no_reduce_keys >= 1\r\n\t    || curbuf->b_term == NULL\r\n\t    || curbuf->b_term->tl_vterm == NULL)\r\n\treturn;\r\n\r\n    if (vterm_using_key_protocol())\r\n    {\r\n\t// \"modify_other_keys\" or kitty keyboard protocol was enabled while\r\n\t// waiting.\r\n\tno_reduce_key_state = NRKS_SET;\r\n\t++no_reduce_keys;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2025-01-09T13:20:49Z",
